CBRE has the pleasure in offering 83-89 Hoxton Park Road, Liverpool NSW 2170, an opportunity moments from Liverpool CBD.

The property is in Liverpool on the corner of Maryvale Avenue and Hoxton Park Road. The site features favourable planning controls, zoned R4 High Density Residential with an FSR of 1:1 and a maximum building height of 15m under the Liverpool Local Environmental Plan 2008. Under this zoning there is currently an approval for 13 apartments.

Some of the key attributes of the property are as follows:

- Development site with a variety of uses
- DA approved for 13 residential apartments
- Site area of 1,516sqm*
- R4 High Density Zoning
- Vacant block of land
- Zoning permits alternate uses such as religious, community, educational, and childcare (STCA)
- Only 3km* to Liverpool CBD

The property is for sale via a Public Auction.

The Auction will be held at Club Marconi on Wednesday 23rd November 2016 at 10:30am.

The property will be auctioned alongside the former Smithfield Post Office.

For any further information, please contact the designated CBRE team:

Frank Oliveri 0419 018 356
Thomas Mosca 0423 086 593

*approx

CBRE is pleased to present this development opportunity at 62 Copeland Street, Liverpool for sale via Public Auction on the 25th of October 2017 at 12:00pm.
 
62 Copeland Street Liverpool is a vacant corner block of R4 High Density residential land on the outskirts of South West Sydney’s capital city. A vacant corner block of land is a rare find, positioned on the of Copeland Street and Moore Street within proximity to Liverpool Westfield, two upcoming Universities, and a direct walk to Liverpool Train Station, TAFE and Bigge Park. 

The key property highlights are as follows:  

- Ideally positioned development site in the heart of Liverpool’s CBD 
- Located on a key corner block with direct access to the Hume Highway/Copeland Street and Moore Street 
- Favourable zoning of R4 High Density Residential which allows for a plethora of residential development options including residential flat building, boarding house, student accommodation – all of which are subject to council approval 
- The site is currently vacant and removed of all improvements which lend benefit to a quick development 
- The site offers a total land area of 533sqm* with and FSR of 2:1 and a height limit of 35m in the immediate area 

Public Auction will be held on Wednesday, 25th October 2017 at 12:00PM.

Auction Location: Gemelle Ristorante - 79 Bathurst St, Liverpool – parking provided on-site 

For further details please contact the below listed agents; 

Ned Mannoun - 0425 25 25 05

Thomas Mosca - 0423 086 593

Alex Mirzaian - 0400 523 523 

*Approx.

Note: all reference to development potential for 62 Copeland Street, Liverpool is subject to council approval and general in use only. CBRE is pleased to present this rare and diverse opportunity at 274 George Street, Liverpool for sale via Public Auction on Saturday 3rd of March 2018 at 10:00am.

274 George Street Liverpool is a two level freehold commercial building in the heart of South West Sydney’s capital - Liverpool. Retail property in the Liverpool CBD seldom presents itself to the market for sale and this provides the opportunity to acquire a very sought-after asset. The Property is positioned in the south-eastern quarter of the CBD, providing close access to Liverpool Station, “Eat Street”, Bigge Park, Western Sydney University (opening 3rd March 2018), University of Wollongong and many more local attractions.

Having good neighbours is always important. Next door we have the new Western Sydney Airport Corporation, Quest Hotels, and the 10,000 m2 commercial building leased by the NSW Government.


The key property highlights are as follows: 

- Extremely versatile holding suiting an investor, developer or owner occupier  
- Current zoning of B3 Commercial Core with a B4 Mixed Use Pending
- Total land area of 194.7sqm* with dual access from Railway Serviceway 
- Existing net income of $58,000 with strategic opportunity leases 
- Total lettable area of 194.7sqm*, split in two levels providing ability of dual income or half occupation and income
- 4 on grade parking spots 
- Pending zoning allows for a small scale, “fine grain” development opportunity such as “student accommodation” or residential units without site amalgamation (subject to council approval and rezoning) 

Public Auction will be held on Saturday – 3rd March 2018 at 10:00am 

Auction Location: On site  

For further details please contact the below listed agents; 

Ned Mannoun - 0425 25 25 05

Thomas Mosca - 0423 086 593

*Approx.

Note: all reference to development potential for 274 George Street, Liverpool is subject to council approval and general in use only. We recommend you conduct your own investigation prior to purchasing this property. CBRE or it’s representatives take no responsibility for the accuracy of this information.

- Site area: 962 square metres*
- Flexible B4 – Mixed Use zoning
